name: undetermined
content:
Add to word list
Add to word list
not measured, counted, or clearly known: The park was developed in several phases, at undetermined costs, between 2015 and 2020. Local residents will be without an emergency water supply for an undetermined length of time.
More examplesFewer examplesThe county fire marshal's office said the cause of the fire is undetermined.A third of these deaths might be classed as undetermined.The selection process for a new chief executive officer will reach a long-awaited conclusion when the executive committee meets at an undetermined location on Sunday.
